<p>What is the length of the unmeasured side of the triangle? <fillin characters="20" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>2.86</li></ul></p><p>Because it does not matter which leg is a and which is b we call the missing leg x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}^{{2}}+{7.54}^{{2}}={8.06}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}^{{2}}+{56.8516}={64.9636}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}^{{2}}={64.9636}-{56.8516}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}^{{2}}={8.112}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle\sqrt{{{x}^{{2}}}}=\sqrt{{{8.112}}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}\approx{2.86}</m>.</p>
</solution>
